verbose_text: DIC uptake in alkaline phototrophic assemblages likely to be dominated by cyanobacteria was unaffected by the addition of 5 muM sulfide, whereas DIC uptake in acidic phototrophic assemblages likely to be dominated by algae was suppressed by sulfide at a concentration of 5 muM.
evidence: DIC uptake in acidic phototrophic assemblages likely to be dominated by algae was suppressed by sulfide
